---->if you want to see the names of the files selected you can refactor your code to this in new.ejs/edit.ejs:
                                <div class="mb-3">
                                  <label class="form-label">Upload Images</label>
                                  <input 
                                      type="file" 
                                      class="form-control" 
                                      name="images" 
                                      id="images"
                                      multiple 
                                      accept="image/*"
                                  >
                                  <div id="fileNames" class="mt-2"></div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <script>
                                  const input = document.getElementById('images');
                                  const fileNamesDiv = document.getElementById('fileNames');
                                
                                  input.addEventListener('change', () => {
                                      const files = Array.from(input.files);
                                      fileNamesDiv.innerHTML = files.map(f => `<p>${f.name}</p>`).join('');
                                  });
                                </script>
----->in the image upload section if you want to limit the size of an image/limit the number of images user can upload at once-->can be improved
